</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BF5808CC369AA9E77934C1BB2C6E5975" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="7A2A348339353C1ED78F720735267317" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C3D19B624A283278D9CF08F0F1657822" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Clearly part of the 
<taxonomicName id="630327316ABDE2D468FE71ACB04940D6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="megapotamica">
<emphasis id="46312D2F181F23BA44BB169B3738709A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea megapotamica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex but immediately recognised by its very large corolla. The (near) glabrous sepals are also distinct.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
